              <h2 class="archive__item-title">Origin and evolution of Earth's magnetic field</h2>
            
          

          
            <div class="archive__item-excerpt">
              <p>I am interested in the origin and evolution of Earth’s magnetic field as well as how it links to processes within Earth’s deep interior. One way to investigate this involves looking at long-term trends in paleointensity records. However, only ~8% (as of 2015, http://earth.liv.ac.uk/pint/) paleointensity determinations are from the Precambrian despite the fact that this time period represents more than 85% of geologic history. Because of this, much of my work thus far has included Precambrian rocks including basalts from the ~1.1Ga Midcontinent Rift.</p>

